=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Multichannel-Expansion_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 501 Hz, featuring punchy attack and percussive envelope, with static spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: static
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 501.0658
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.2142
  harmonic_regularity: 0.2194
  pitch_clarity: 6.3713
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -20.5730
  resonance_freq: 3509.9121

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Multichannel Expansion Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Multichannel-Expansion.html
// Tags: Multichannel-Expansion, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 3 ---
{ Blip.ar(500,8,0.1) }.play // one channel

// the array in the freq input causes an Array of 2 Blips to be created :
{ Blip.ar([499,600],8,0.1) }.play // two channels

Blip.ar(500,8,0.1).postln // one unit generator created.

Blip.ar([500,601],8,0.1).postln // two unit generators created.
